3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach for modeling complex non-rigid deformations, which is a common problem in AI applications such as robotics and animation. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possible category as the paper addresses the problem of modeling non-rigid deformations in images, which is a common problem in computer graphics. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with the problem of structure-from-motion, which is a common problem in multimedia applications such as video processing and 3D reconstruction.
